whereas.text:
Whereas linemen are often first responders during storms
			 and other catastrophic events, working to make the scene safe for other public
			 safety heroes;

Whereas linemen work with thousands of volts of
			 electricity high atop power lines 24 hours a day, 365 days a year, to keep
			 electricity flowing;

Whereas linemen must often work under dangerous conditions
			 far from their families to construct and maintain the energy infrastructure of
			 the United States;

Whereas linemen put their lives on the line every day with
			 little recognition from the community regarding the danger of their work;
			 and
